criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  primary HCC diagnosed by a surgeon and/or radiologist and oncologist according to the
             international guidelines for the management of HCC or by pathology

          -  single lesion and longest tumor diameter were 5-10cm;

          -  CP-A or B classification;

          -  Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) score 0-1;

          -  distances between tumor and normal organs (esophagus, stomach, duodenum, bowel) are
             more than 5 mm

          -  unsuitable for other therapies, such as patients with heart disease, uncontrolled
             diabetes, uncontrolled hypertension, etc.

          -  rejecting other therapies such as resection, liver transplantation, etc.

          -  platelet count≥50 × 109/L, white blood count≥1.5 × 109/L;

          -  patients infected with hepatitis B virus who are treated with adefovir or entecavir;
             patients infected with hepatitis C virus whose HCV DNA are negative.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  tumor thrombus;

          -  lymph node involvement;

          -  extrahepatic metastasis.
